  "response": "No, NEdit (Nirvana Editor) does not support the insertion of images or pictures. NEdit is primarily a text editor focused on editing plain text and code. It does not have the capability to handle non-text elements such as images. If you need to include images in your documents, you might want to use a word processor or a more advanced text editor that supports rich text formatting and multimedia elements, such as Microsoft Word, LibreOffice Writer, or Markdown editors that can handle image links.",
